# Repository license notice

This repository is a research artifact. Its contents have different provenance and redistribution constraints.

## Original experiment code, configs, and documentation

Unless a file states otherwise, the newly written experiment orchestration scripts, configuration templates, documentation, and result-table utilities in this repository may be used, modified, and redistributed for non-commercial academic research with attribution.

## Architecture implementations and third-party-derived code

Files under `src/models/` include architecture implementations and adaptations related to TransXNet, EdgeNeXt, RepViT, timm, MMCV, and related public research code. These components retain the licenses and citation requirements of their original upstream projects. See `THIRD_PARTY_NOTICES.md` and the manuscript references.

## Paper assets

The manuscript text, figures, and tables under `paper/` are provided for scholarly review and citation. Reuse outside review, citation, or fair academic discussion requires permission from the corresponding author unless otherwise stated.

## Excluded artifacts

No license is granted here for original medical image datasets, trained checkpoints, ONNX binaries, APK files, or third-party dataset annotations. Those artifacts are not redistributed in this repository.

## No warranty

The material is provided as-is for research and reproducibility review. No clinical, diagnostic, or commercial use is authorized by this repository notice.
